// Sitecore Helix solution Gulp building

Configuring Gulp: -
Go to Habitat package and copy the folder gulp-config.js, gulpfile.js, package.json and scripts folder and paste it at C:\Source - Local\ProjectName
From Visual Studio, add gulp-config.js, gulpfile.js, package.json as existing items to the Configuration Solution folder created earlier.
To install the Node modules, open cmd promt in admin right at location C:\Source - Local\ProjectName and run command “npm install”
If command is executed successfully, you should be able to check the gulf task from our Task Runner Explorer.
Run the command one by one to perform required operations. For example, click on Publish-All-Projects and you should all the dlls published to the deployed folder at location C:\inetpub\wwwroot\AandH\Website\bin.
